{
  "number": 259,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/259",
  "title": "[headerFooter]: CSS classes",
  "body": "How do you imagine the CSS classes added to the various `root`, `header`, `body`, `footer` element created through the `headerFooter` decorator?\n\nI imagine something like that:\n\n``` html\n<div class=\"ais-widget-name {{cssClasses.root}}\">\n  <div class=\"ais-widget-name--header {{cssClasses.header}}\"></div>\n  <div class=\"ais-widget-name--body {{cssClasses.body}}\"></div>\n  <div class=\"ais-widget-name--footer {{cssClasses.footer}}\"></div>\n</div>\n```\n\nWith `cssClasses` being the attribute passed to the widget so user can add custom classes. \n\nDo you think we should also add more generic `ais-header`, `ais-footer` classes everytime the decorator is called. This could help us always style headers the same way easily, but this also means we will have to add `ais-root` and `ais-body` classes that do not make a lot of sense.\n\nI'm in favor of not adding the `ais-header` and `ais-footer` in a first version. Agreed?\n",
  "created_at": "2015-10-16T08:50:06Z",
